## This session: author a new APIARY

You are creating a new apiary on disk for this operator. The apiary is
the unit of work in r2-composer — one deployment with one TG and one
class string.

## Read these FIRST, in this order

1. `specifications/SPEC-APIARY-CREATE.md` — **the normative workflow**.
   Read it end-to-end. §2 (the five-step user journey) and §3 (the
   atomicity contract) are the rules you operate under. §8 lists the
   error codes you may emit on failure.

2. `specifications/SPEC-APIARY-LAYOUT.md` — the underlying directory +
   `apiary.toml` schema you scaffold against.

3. `specifications/SPEC-APIARY-COMPOSE.md` §4 — the `[[role_ensembles.targets]]`
   shape if the operator already knows their composition. New apiaries
   typically start with zero role-ensembles; that's fine.

4. The canonical existing example: `apiaries/rocker-rig/apiary.toml`
   (authored 2026-06-01 from SPEC-APIARY-COMPOSE §12). Read it to see
   the shape an apiary takes when it has 4 role-ensembles + 6 targets.

## What you MUST produce

Per SPEC-APIARY-CREATE §2.3 the initial scaffold REQUIRES:

- `apiaries/<name>/apiary.toml` — structured contract per §3 of
  SPEC-APIARY-LAYOUT. Initially with zero `[[role_ensembles]]`.
- `apiaries/<name>/README.md` — one paragraph operator-narrative.
- `apiaries/<name>/AI-CONTEXT.md` — fresh-CC brief; cites this spec +
  the apiary's name, class, class-hash.
- `apiaries/<name>/trust_keys/tg_pub.bin` + `tg_meta.toml` — Ed25519
  public material + SHA-256 fingerprint (§2.2).
- `apiaries/<name>/devices/roster.toml` — empty (`[devices]` header only).
- `apiaries/<name>/.gitignore` — verbatim from SPEC-APIARY-CREATE Annex A.
- `apiaries/<name>/conversation/<date>-create-apiary-01.md` — transcript.
- `git init -b main` + first commit per §2.4.
- `~/.config/r2-composer/apiaries/<name>/tg_signer/tg_priv.bin` (mode 0600,
  parent dir 0700) per §2.2.

This is an ATOMIC TRANSACTION (§3). Either all of the above succeed
together or you delete everything and emit `r2.composer.author.error`.

## Constraints

- Apiary name MUST match `^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9._-]*$` and MUST NOT collide
  with an existing `apiaries/<name>/` directory.
- Class string MUST be reverse-DNS per R2-CAP §3.
- Private key NEVER in-tree; only at the off-tree path above.
- TG keypair: generate fresh (default) unless operator says "import".
- Calm-computing: one ambient italic chat line per file written.

## How to ask clarifying questions

Operator's first message is below. Per SPEC-APIARY-CREATE §2.1, you
elicit name + class + description through conversation — propose
candidates, don't demand structured input. If the operator's message
already supplies all three, skip ahead to confirmation.

